{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Finding emotions correlated with gives concepts\n","\n","Same concepts in different religions can be associated with different views and emotions. This notebook focuses on exploration of words' emotional description. Since emotional reaction is usually expressed in a form of adjectives, this will be a goal of our exploration.\n","\n","For a given words (eg. god, faith) we look for the synonyms across all generated models, one holy text at a time. This step contains searching for the most similar words and filtering out parts of speech not matching given, initial word. From the results we pick best 4-5 synonyms by hand.\n","\n","For found synonyms we subsequently look for the adjectives that are the best description of these synonyms. Again, we facilitate part-of-speech-based filtering.\n","\n","*To mitigate radnom factor of the embeddings' training, 30 models were generated for each corpus using Word2Vec training (for more details please look at the 'Training' notebook).*"],"metadata":{"id":"15UNzWqZgTvA"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"XHR3vndd_B5_"},"source":["# Libraries"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"_taewaEk6LBU"},"outputs":[],"source":["!pip install -U cade\n","!pip install git+https://github.com/valedica/gensim.git\n","!pip install gensim"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"xRG3sCEOBrBW","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1656100727575,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":3763,"user":{"displayName":"Tomasz Stanislaw Grzesiak","userId":"10010938413380139007"}},"outputId":"737e0fdd-a40e-4841-c72f-a7f6838dfc31"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["[nltk_data] Downloading package punkt to /root/nltk_data...\n","[nltk_data]   Unzipping tokenizers/punkt.zip.\n","[nltk_data] Downloading package averaged_perceptron_tagger to\n","[nltk_data]     /root/nltk_data...\n","[nltk_data]   Unzipping taggers/averaged_perceptron_tagger.zip.\n"]}],"source":["import os\n","from gensim.models import Word2Vec\n","import nltk\n","nltk.download('punkt')\n","nltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger')\n","from nltk.corpus import wordnet\n","from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n","from typing import List"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":41721,"status":"ok","timestamp":1656100783050,"user":{"displayName":"Tomasz Stanislaw Grzesiak","userId":"10010938413380139007"},"user_tz":-120},"id":"_Htx9fNqqV4P","outputId":"650f50ed-eaa0-40b6-f7bd-541e38ae8f57"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Mounted at /content/drive\n"]}],"source":["from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')\n","os.chdir('/content/drive/MyDrive/Project Data Semantics /Embeddings_W2VEC_nl')\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Explore models"],"metadata":{"id":"OkuZ9InyZ2fg"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Load models for later use"],"metadata":{"id":"G2lFGRa51AlT"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["number_of_models = 30\n","\n","models = dict(bible = [], quran = [], tripitaka = [], vedas_upanishads = [])\n","for i in range(number_of_models):\n","  models['bible'].append(Word2Vec.load('Bible_embeddings/bible_' + str(i) + '.model'))\n","  models['quran'].append(Word2Vec.load('Quran_embeddings/quran_' + str(i) + '.model'))\n","  models['tripitaka'].append(Word2Vec.load('Tripitaka_embeddings/tripitaka_' + str(i) + '.model'))\n","  models['vedas_upanishads'].append(Word2Vec.load('VedasUpanishads_embeddings/vedasupanishads_' + str(i) + '.model'))"],"metadata":{"id":"OpKED6CO0_hS"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Words to explore"],"metadata":{"id":"W9xTmhg2mR65"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["words_to_explore = ['god', 'faith', 'heaven', 'evil']"],"metadata":{"id":"QsxpNjcGmPrF"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###Finding synonymes\n","\n","Find 10 most similar descriptions of given word (God, Heaven, faith, etc.)"],"metadata":{"id":"UYM-vE__wTdz"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def check_pos_tag(word: str, tag_prefix: str) -> bool:\n","  part_of_speech = nltk.pos_tag(word_tokenize(word))[0][1]\n","  return part_of_speech.startswith(tag_prefix)\n","\n","def is_noun(word: str) -> bool:\n","  return check_pos_tag(word, 'NN')\n","\n","def is_adjective(word: str) -> bool:\n","  return check_pos_tag(word, 'JJ')"],"metadata":{"id":"FEuGb-KqP7fn"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def find_similar(word: str, n_synonyms: int, pos_tag_prefix: str, models: List[Word2Vec]) -> List[str]: #word to explore, number of synonyms we want, used model\n","\n","  highest_rated_nouns = dict()\n","\n","  for i in range(number_of_models):\n","    # get list of the most similar words in single model, filtered by part of speech\n","    synonyms = models[i].wv.most_similar(word, topn=(5*n_synonyms))\n","    synonyms_nouns = list(filter(lambda synonym: check_pos_tag(synonym[0], pos_tag_prefix), synonyms))\n","\n","    # combine words from different models\n","    for (noun, similarity) in synonyms_nouns:\n","      if noun not in highest_rated_nouns.keys():\n","        highest_rated_nouns[noun] = similarity\n","      else:\n","        highest_rated_nouns[noun] = max(highest_rated_nouns[noun], similarity)\n","\n","  # sort nouns by similarity (desc.) and select specified number of them\n","  highest_rated_nouns_sorted = sorted(highest_rated_nouns.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)[:n_synonyms]\n","  synonyms_nouns = [w for (w, sim) in highest_rated_nouns_sorted]\n","\n","  return synonyms_nouns\n","\n","\n","def find_synonyms_nouns(word: str, n_synonyms: int, models: List[Word2Vec]) -> List[str]:\n","  return find_similar(word, n_synonyms, 'NN', models)\n","\n","def find_describing_adjectives(words: List[str], n_adjectives: int, models: List[Word2Vec]) -> None:\n","  for word in words:\n","    print(find_similar(word, n_adjectives, 'JJ', models))"],"metadata":{"id":"6QhQi6tmwc76"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["for word_to_explore in words_to_explore:\n","  for holy_text, model_list in models.items():\n","    print(f\"{word_to_explore} - {holy_text}: {find_synonyms_nouns(word_to_explore, 10, model_list)}\")\n","  print()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"CCaAcYES7aQL","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1656101014614,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":12958,"user":{"displayName":"Tomasz Stanislaw Grzesiak","userId":"10010938413380139007"}},"outputId":"ce433a9b-d504-4f9a-ce59-4b5e9cc85f2e"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["god - bible: ['lord', 'saviour', 'yah', 'mindful', 'redeemer', 'savior', 'forevermore', 'evermore', 'confession', 'stablish']\n","god - quran: ['allah', 'allfill', 'alliih', 'allih', 'seeth', 'bondmen', 'cherishes', 'allmerciful', 'pleaseth', 'allwise']\n","god - tripitaka: ['śuddhāvāsa', 'tuṣita', 'yama', 'brahmakāyika', 'trāyastriṃśa', 'nirmāṇarati', 'paranirmitavaśavartin', 'bṛhatphala', 'akaniṣṭha', 'brahma']\n","god - vedas_upanishads: ['stimulate', 'savitar', 'cherish', 'impulse', 'savitr', 'checks', 'savity', 'quadruped', 'blissful', 'purifier']\n","\n","faith - bible: ['afflictions', 'unbelief', 'perseverance', 'patience', 'grace', 'gentleness', 'endurance', 'sufferings', 'gospel', 'patient']\n","faith - quran: ['belief', 'virtue', 'attitude', 'contributions', 'unbelief', 'strengthens', 'steadfastness', 'obscure', 'profess', 'opponents']\n","faith - tripitaka: ['trust', 'essences', 'forbearance', 'adherence', 'possesses', 'diligence', 'honest', 'steadfast', 'concentrate', 'attitude']\n","faith - vedas_upanishads: ['strives', 'flaw', 'whenever', 'stablish', 'needs', 'decisive', 'hearer', 'serveth', 'immediate', 'aye']\n","\n","heaven - bib